race.comment: Fascinating race to kick off Cup Day, where a few well-bred first-starters from top stables loom as key players. One of them is IMPONDERABLE (12), a daughter of So You Think, who had blinkers added for her most recent jumpout, which sparked massive improvement. She showed a swift turn of foot rounding the home turn and cleared out for a massive win. The blinkers stay on here and 1450m on debut looks suitable. PAVLICH (7) looks the best of the raced brigade, beaten half-a-length when third on debut after blowing the start, and that race experience could prove crucial here. KING'S ANCHOR (6) is a first-starter from the McEvoy yard who's won his last two trials. Bit of a gap to the rest, the best of whom might be ACANTILADO (1), who will be better for a couple of runs back.
